          "type": "text",
          "value": "A key difference between internet content and broadcast TV is that the airwaves are a rivalrous good; two broadcasters cannot occupy the same frequency, in the same region, at the same time. In order for the public to benefit from broadcast communication someone had to regulate broadcasting."
