          "type": "text",
          "value": "The 1985 Plaza Accord is an example of the US Treasury working in coordination with other nations to achieve such a dollar devaluation. [2] Yet in our current high-inflation environment such an intervention would be incredibly unpopular. The historical analogous Plaza Accord was only possible after the Fed had sufficiently vanquished inflation earlier in the 80s. Similar to today, the dollar appreciated significantly throughout this hawkish monetary policy, yet US domestic politics could not consider the broader implications until inflation was addressed."
