          "value": "Are you referring to Summers\u2019 advocacy for the repeal of Glass\u2013Steagall via  Gramm\u2013Leach\u2013Bliley Act? If so, that legislation had little if any impact on the financial crisis. The separation of commercial and investment banks via GS was irrelevant since all of the problematic financial firms were pure investment banks. E.g., Lehman, Bear Stearns, and Merrill Lynch."
